<section class="section">
  <div class="page-shell legal-page prose">
    <h2>Independent and unofficial</h2>
    <p>
      Cert Happens is an independent study resource. It is not affiliated with,
      sponsored by, approved by, or endorsed by CompTIA or any other certification
      vendor unless a page explicitly states otherwise.
    </p>

    <h2>Trademarks</h2>
    <p>
      CompTIA, Security+, and related marks are trademarks of CompTIA, Inc. Other
      certification names, product names, and trademarks belong to their respective
      owners. Their use identifies the certifications or technologies discussed.
    </p>

    <h2>Practice content</h2>
    <p>
      Practice questions are original study material designed around publicly
      available exam objectives and generally accepted technical concepts. They are
      not copied exam questions and should not be treated as a prediction of the exact
      questions that will appear on an official exam.
    </p>

    <h2>Scores and readiness</h2>
    <p>
      A Cert Happens percentage is a practice score. It is not an official
      vendor-scaled score and does not guarantee exam readiness or a passing result.
      Small randomized domain samples should not be treated as mastery ratings.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy and updates</h2>
    <p>
      The site aims to provide accurate and useful material, but technical standards,
      vendor objectives, terminology, and recommended practices can change. Questions
      and explanations may contain errors or become outdated.
    </p>

    <h2>Report an issue</h2>
    <p>
      Use the <strong>Report question</strong> control on a live test or results review
      when a question may contain a typo, unclear explanation, incorrect answer,
      duplicate, or outdated concept.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
